kf, scoring='r2')\nprint('Cross val Score:', np.mean(scores))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T18:31:27.329204Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T18:31:27.329892Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.416923Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-07T18:31:27.329849Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.416081Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Cross val Score: 0.9682799478078561\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":10},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Optuna (Bayesian optimization)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-06T18:25:35.704249Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-06T18:25:35.704623Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-06T18:25:35.709489Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-06T18:25:35.704592Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-06T18:25:35.708358Z"}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#!pip install optuna\n\nimport optuna","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.417942Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.418267Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.423135Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.418238Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.421827Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":11},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Optuna** is a tool used to **automatically find the best hyperparameters** for machine learning models.\n### Simple Idea\nInstead of manually trying different settings, Optuna:\n- Tries many combinations\n- Learns from past trials\n- Finds the best settings faster\n\n### Key Features\n- **Automatic tuning** of hyperparameters  \n- **Efficient search** (tries smart combinations)  \n- **Pruning** → stops bad trials early to save time  \n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Optuna Objective Function\n\n**Definition:**  \nThe **objective function** in Optuna is the function that evaluates a set of hyperparameters and returns a performance score. Optuna uses this score to find the best hyperparameters.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Purpose:** Tell Optuna how good a model is for given hyperparameters.  \n- **Returns:** A single value (e.g., RMSE, R²) to **minimize** or **maximize**.  \n- **Structure:**\n  1. Suggest hyperparameters using `trial.suggest_*`\n  2. Train your model with these hyperparameters\n  3. Evaluate the model on validation data\n  4. Return the performance metric\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def objective(trial):\n\n    #hyperparameter\n    params = {\n         \"max_depth\" : trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 1, 10),\n    \"min_samples_split\" : trial.suggest_int('min_samples_split', 2, 10),\n    \"min_samples_leaf\" : trial.suggest_int('min_samples_leaf', 1, 5)}\n\n    #model\n    model =  DecisionTreeRegressor(**params, random_state=42)\n\n    # cross-validation\n    kf=KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n    scores=cross_val_score(model1, X_train, y_train, cv=kf, scoring='r2')\n\n    return np.mean(scores)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.424496Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.424783Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.451287Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.424755Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.450271Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":12},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Optuna Trial\n\n**Definition:**  \nA **Trial** in Optuna represents a **single run of the objective function** with a specific set of hyperparameters. Each trial evaluates the model and returns a score.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Purpose:** Track **one combination of hyperparameters** and its performance.\n- **Hyperparameter suggestions:** Use `trial.suggest_*` methods:\n  ```python\n  learning_rate = trial.suggest_float(\"learning_rate\", 0.01, 0.2)\n  max_depth = trial.suggest_int(\"max_depth\", 2, 6)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Optuna Study\n\n**Definition:**  \nA **Study** in Optuna is the **object that manages the optimization process**. It keeps track of all trials, hyperparameters tested, and their evaluation results.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Purpose:** Coordinate the search for the best hyperparameters.  \n- **Contains:**  \n  - All trials and their results  \n  - Best hyperparameters found  \n  - Optimization direction (`minimize` or `maximize`)  ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from optuna.samplers import TPESampler\n# Create the study\nstudy = optuna.create_study( direction='maximize',  sampler=TPESampler())\n\n# Run the optimization\nstudy.optimize(objective, n_trials=50)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.452361Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.452704Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-07T18:31:29.538099Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-07T18:31:28.452668Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-07T18:31:29.537211Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"[I 2026-04-07 18:31:28,470] A new study created in memory with name: no-name-004ce7e9-affa-4658-8c5b-7ebf389e2157\n[I 2026-04-07 18:31:29,534] Trial 0 finished with value: 0.9682799478078561 and parameters: {'max_depth': 5, 'min_samples_split': 6, 'min_samples_leaf': 5}. Best is trial 0 with value: 0.9682799478078561.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":13},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Optuna Sampler & Direction\n\n**Definition:**  \nIn Optuna, the **sampler** decides **how to choose hyperparameters** for each trial.  \nThe **direction** tells Optuna whether it should **maximize or minimize** the objective function.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Sampler:** Suggests hyperparameter values (`trial.suggest_*`) based on past trials.\n  - Examples: `TPESampler`, `RandomSampler`\n- **Direction:** Indicates optimization goal for the study.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(study.best_trial.value)   #print the best hyper paramater value\nprint(study.best_trial.params)  ","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.